Basic Arithmetic Instructions

ADD – addition

      x = a + b

SUB – subtraction

      x = a - b

MUL – multiplication

      x = a * b

DIV – division (integer or floating-point, depending on the data type)

      x = a / b

INC / DEC – increment / decrement

      INC x
      DEC x



Logical and Bitwise Instructions

AND, OR, XOR – logical/bitwise operations

      x = a AND b

NOT – bitwise negation

      x = NOT a

SHL / SHR – bit shifting

      x = SHL(a, 1)

ROL / ROR – bit rotation

      x = ROL(a, 1)

Memory Instructions

POKE – write to a memory address

      POKE &H80000000, 255

PEEK – read from a memory address

      value = PEEK(&H80000000)

MOV – move or copy a value (syntactic sugar for assignment)

      MOV x, y

MALLOC / FREE – dynamic memory management

      p = MALLOC(1024)
      FREE p


CPU Registers and Control

REGGET / REGSET – access CPU registers

      REGSET "A", 5
      x = REGGET("SP")

FLAGS – manipulate processor flags

REGSET "FLAGS", REGGET("FLAGS") OR &H200

CLI / STI – disable or enable interrupts

    CLI
    STI
    Control Flow
    IF / THEN / ELSE / END IF
    FOR / TO / STEP / NEXT
    WHILE / WEND
    DO / LOOP UNTIL
    GOTO / GOSUB / RETURN

These instructions provide the standard program flow. Although GOTO is generally discouraged, it remains useful for certain low-level programming tasks.

Interrupts and System Calls

ON INTERRUPT n GOTO label – register an interrupt service routine (ISR)

IRET – return from an interrupt handler

SYS id, param1, param2... – invoke a system call

      SYS 1, p, size
      result = SYS(2)

I/O Ports

OUT port, value – write to an I/O port

      OUT &H3F8, 65

IN(port) – read from an I/O port

      value = IN(&H3F8)
      Inline Assembly

ASM ... END ASM – embed native assembly code

      ASM
          MOV AX, 1234h
          OUT 60h, AX
      END ASM


Threads / Processes (Optional)

Create and manage execution threads.

      THREAD START func, priority
      
      THREAD YIELD
      
      THREAD SLEEP ms

Debugging and System

TRACE ON / OFF – enable or disable instruction tracing

DUMP addr, len – display a memory dump

PANIC msg – trigger a kernel panic

      TRACE ON

      DUMP &H80000000, 128

      PANIC "Kernel Fault"
